for the truth.

14
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:09,750
Got it.

15
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,090
Let's get a drink

16
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,440
to relax.

17
00:02:21,460 --> 00:02:22,270
Mr. Shen.

18
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,530
Mr. Shen.

19
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:35,870
You really surprised me today.

20
00:02:36,370 --> 00:02:39,030
It's normal for someone like me to do dirty work.

21
00:02:39,370 --> 00:02:40,370
It's my duty.

22
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:42,579
But you are

23
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:46,300
always well-dressed and righteous,

24
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:50,220
yet you also drop the ball at critical moments.

25
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,870
I really thought you'd speak for the people

26
00:02:52,870 --> 00:02:55,050
at the press conference today.

27
00:02:56,570 --> 00:02:59,170
How does it feel to clean up Mr. Kang's mess?

28
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:11,780
And you.

29
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,780
I used to be passionate

30
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:18,380
and upright

31
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:20,870
like you.

32
00:03:23,350 --> 00:03:25,030
But after going through a lot,

33
00:03:25,579 --> 00:03:26,790
I've matured.

34
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:28,829
Don't worry.

35
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,850
You'll become like me soon.

36
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:34,790
Take care.

37
00:04:27,110 --> 00:04:28,550
Sir, I don't understand.

38
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,800
Why aren't...

39
00:04:33,350 --> 00:04:34,790
good people

40
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:35,580
rewarded?

41
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:39,400
As the old saying goes,

42
00:04:40,670 --> 00:04:42,200
"Evildoers get gold belts;

43
00:04:42,340 --> 00:04:44,800
good people can't even keep their corpses."

44
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,670
It's always been like this.

45
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,600
But have they forgotten

46
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,030
Sun Yat-sen's last wish?

47
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:53,710
Or

48
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,990
do oaths

49
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:58,090
mean nothing?

50
00:04:58,110 --> 00:04:59,190
Some join the party

51
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:02,160
to change China.

52
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:04,810
Others join

53
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,860
for prestige and fortune.

54
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,650
We can't demand others to change.

55
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:10,940
We can only stay true

56
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:14,700
to our beliefs.

57
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,560
Did you stay true to your beliefs?

58
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:18,600
Is this the result you wanted?

59
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,440
No.

60
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,740
Of course not.

61
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,040
Mr. Song promised me

62
00:05:37,290 --> 00:05:38,409
that this case

63
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,550
will be submitted to Chairman Chiang,

64
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:42,740
and he'd punish whomever deserves it,

65
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,450
even if it's his family.

66
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:45,610
Counterfeit coins

67
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,180
will never appear in Shanghai again

68
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:49,320
and the opium will be destroyed secretly.

69
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,150
I know it's not enough, but...

70
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:53,840
But what we did

71
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,700
was

72
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,540
not in vain.

73
